## Component Specifications

### Navigation
- Fixed position, top of page
- Glassmorphism background (blur 20px)
- Logo left, links right
- Active link has accent color + bottom indicator
- Mobile: hamburger menu

### Upload Zone
- Max width 800px, centered
- Large padding (64px)
- Glassmorphism card
- Animated gradient border (flows around perimeter)
- States: default, dragover (scale up slightly, brighter border), uploading
- Upload icon (cloud with arrow)
- "Drop your file here" title
- "or click to browse" subtitle
- Format badges: .PDF .DOCX in mono font
- "Maximum file size: 10MB" muted text

### Scan Button
- Full width below upload zone
- Gradient background (accent gradient)
- Glow shadow
- Disabled state: 50% opacity, no glow
- Hover: lift up 2px, stronger glow
- Loading: spinner + "Scanning..." text

### Results Summary Cards
- 4 cards in a row (grid)
- Each card: severity color top border (3px)
- Large count number in severity color
- Label below in muted text
- Glassmorphism background

### Finding Cards
- Left border colored by severity (4px)
- Badge showing subtype (mono font, uppercase)
- Severity label (uppercase, colored)
- Description text
- Code block for content/URL/value (mono font, dark bg)
- Location indicator (Page X / Paragraph Y)

### Custom Cursor
- Hide default cursor everywhere
- Main ring: 40px circle, accent border, follows with lerp delay
- Center dot: 6px, accent fill, instant follow
- Hover state: ring expands to 60px
- Click state: ring shrinks to 30px
- Disabled on touch devices

## Animation Guidelines
- Transitions: 0.2s-0.3s ease or ease-out
- Use transform and opacity for performance
- Cursor: requestAnimationFrame loop
- Scroll reveals: IntersectionObserver with threshold 0.1
- Page transitions: fade out 300ms, navigate, fade in

## API Integration
- POST /api/analyze with FormData
- Handle loading state
- Handle errors gracefully
- On success: hide upload section, show results
- "Scan Another" button resets to upload view

## Do Not
- Use any CSS framework
- Use any JS framework
- Use emojis
- Use generic placeholder images
- Make it look like Bootstrap/Tailwind templates